<p>It’s a SequentialCommandGroup.  We’re trying to spin the various subsystem motors for a specified amount of time.</p>
<p>To help debug we exposed a method in the DriveSubsystem that sets the speed directly on the motor controller groups.  That command is called SetDriveSpeedCommand.   It works.  It’s when we try to move the robot using our GrandTheftDriveCommand (which the gtaDrive method of our DriveSubsystem) that it doesn’t move.  gtaDrive calls tankDrive.</p>
<p>GrandTheftDriveCommand works in Teleop and it’s our default DriveSubsystem command.  Any ideas?</p>
